<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Contemn" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Contemn,</orth> to despise: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.289" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 289</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 3, 46</bibl> (Ff. <emph>contenuing, contending</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.161" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 150</bibl> (by conjecture). <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.6.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 6, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 41</bibl>. <cit><quote>what am I that thou shouldst c. me this?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 204" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 204</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>This</emph>).
